Title : S. Samar Hasnain
Text : '''S. Samar Hasnain''' [[Fellow of the Royal Society of Chemistry|FRSC]] is the [[Max Perutz]] professor of [[Molecular Biophysics]] at the [[University of Liverpool]]. He is current [[editor in chief]] of IUCr Journals. In 1991 he became a [[Fellow of the Institute of Physics]] and in 2002 he became a [[Fellow of the Royal Society of Chemistry]]. Additionally, in 1997 he became a [[Third World Academy of Sciences|Fellow of the Third World Academy of Sciences]] and in 2011 a [[Fellow of the Society of Biology]].<ref name="crystal">{{cite web|url=http://www.iucr.org/news/newsletter/volume-20/number-3/new-editor-in-chief|title=New Editor-in-Chief|last=Editor-in-chief|first=|date=|publisher=[[International Union of Crystallography]]|format=Web page|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|work=|accessdate=13 March 2017}}</ref><ref name=univliv/>

==Background==
In 1970 Hasnain earned a Bachelor of Science (Honours) an M.Sc. in 1972 and a Ph.D. in 1977. His research areas include [[neurodegenerative disease]]s, methodical [[drug discovery]], [[protein crystallography]], and [[synchrotron radiation]].<ref name=univliv>
